The paper discusses a novel approach to analyzing joint signal and network dynamics using graphs, which is relevant to several sub-fields in computer science. The use of graphs suggests a focus on network analysis, which is reflected in the likely sub-categories of cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing). The paper also presents methods for analyzing multivariate signals, which could fall under cs.LG (machine learning) or cs.SD (sound and music computing). Finally, the paper discusses applications in geophysics, which could fall under cs.IT (information theory).
